<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Simon Technology Center Library Assistant (Assistive Technology Center)</a></h2>

<p>
<strong>POSITION</strong>: Simon Technology Center Library Assistant (Assistive Technology Center)<br />
<strong>SUPERVISOR</strong>: Bridget Ames, Coordinator of the Simon Technology 
Center<br />
<strong>STATUS</strong>: Part-time, Tuesdays 4 p.m. to 6 p.m. and Saturdays 10 a.m. to 4 p.m.
</p>

<p><strong><em>
The PACER Simon Technology Center Library is a software and assistive device preview service for families and professionals in Minnesota who have or work with children or adults with disabilities. Assistive technology is used to help individuals with disabilities to reach their full potential. 
</em></strong></p>


<h3>Responsibilities:</h3>
<ol>
	<li>Provide respectful service to families and professionals by answering questions regarding membership and programs. </li>
	<li>Assist members in using software and devices during open library times. </li>
	<li>Administer the checking in and out of library items.</li>
	<li>Ensure proper mailing of software and devices to members throughout Minnesota.</li>
	<li>Test software and devices for functional usage and operating system compliance.</li>
	<li>Assist in keeping the library organized by reshelving items and cleaning devices.</li>
	<li>Provide data entry tasks as needed.</li>
	<li>Other general library duties as assigned.</li>
	<li>Participate in Open House and other PACER activities as needed</li>
</ol>

<h3>Required Qualifications</h3>
<ol>
	<li>Great customer service skills</li>
	<li>A friendly and energetic personality</li>
	<li>Attention to detail and organizational strategies</li>
	<li>Knowledge of computer, internet, software and data entry tasks</li>
	<li>Interest and experience working with children with disabilities</li>
	<li>Strong verbal and written communication skills</li>
</ol>

<p>
Parents of children and young adults with disabilities are encouraged to apply.<br />
Salary will be based on experience and qualifications.
</p>

<p>Submit resume with cover letter to:<br />
Sandy Loehnis | PACER Center |
8161 Normandale Blvd | Minneapolis, MN 55437</p>

<p>
PACER Center is an <em>Affirmative Action and Equal Opportunity</em> Employer.&nbsp;
</p>

